     SubsurfaceTopics is the quarterly newsletter for the Subsurface Science
        Initiative. Newsletter topics include program activities, updates on
      development of the planned Subsurface Geosciences Laboratory, features
         on specific research projects, hiring announcements, and updates on
     research collaborations and partnerships. Sign up to get on our mailing
                                                                       list.

   Newsletter Archives:
   Current Issue:
   December 2001, Vol.2 Issue 4
   Topics: Stimulating biogeochemical reactions to sequester strontium;
   Dr. Gill Geesey--new SSI Biosciences Discipline Lead; LASIMS research
   yields unexpected results; Investigating fate and mobility of
   actinides, fission products and other contaminants; Triangulating on
   the ESRP Aquifer; Board lauds progress--urges intensified science
   planning; New SSI/INRA liaison. [html] [pdf]

   September 2001, Vol. 2 Issue 3
   Topics: SGL facility conceptual design contact awarded; Center for
   Science and Technology breaks ground; Inland Northwest Research
   Alliance; Unsaturated Zone Interest Group (UZIG) annual get-together;
   Initiatives notes. [html] [pdf]

   Previous Issues:
   July 2001, Vol. 2 Issue 2
   Topics: Vadose zone research park established; New geosciences
   technical lead appointed; Vadose zone roadmap nears completion;
   Initiative Notes; Mobile laboratory expands field capabilities; $5
   million awarded for Eastern Idaho Science and Research Center. [pdf]

   January 2001, Vol. 2 Issue 1
   Topics: Director appointed to Subsurface Science Initiative; Dr.
   Russell Hertzog accepts technical lead position in physics; Subsurface
   Peer Review Board appointed; LDRD Awards; Research trip to VEGAS;
   Analysis identifies gaps in DOE's environmental research; INEEL builds
   large-scale lysimeter; What is the INEEL?; Initiatives notes.  [pdf]

   July 2000, Vol. 1 Issue 2
   Topics: INEEL hosts mesoscale subsurface research workshop; INEEL
   continues recruiting for subsurface science initiative; INEEL issues
   LDRD Calls for 2001 proposals; Visiting graduate student spurs INEEL
   research; Enzymes a key to measuring subsurface pollution; Chemically
   assisted composting applied to TNT-contaminated soils; Initiative web
   site to be launched; Initiatives notes. [pdf]

   March 2000, Vol.1 Issue 1
   Topics: INEEL establishes subsurface science initiative; message from
   INEEL Laboratory Director Billy Shipp; INEEL conducts initial workshop
   with partner universities; DOE's top scientist visits INEEL; Enhancing
   capabilities and building collaborative partnerships. [pdf]


